<item>
            <title>[LU-9507] o2iblnd assert on reconnect</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9507</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;An assert in kiblnd_reconnect_peer() is being hit. With the multi-qp patch, it is possible to have ibp_connecting to be &amp;gt; 0. Since one connection can fail, and an attempt to reconnect can occur, while the other connections are still being established.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Discussed with Doug and this assert should be changed to an if statement, to log when this situation occurs instead of asserting.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
